The following general principles will direct the Republic of Croatia towards sustainable development:
* protection of human health;
* promotion and protection of fundamental rights;
* solidarity within and between generations;
* open and democratic society;
* involvement of citizens;
* involvement of businesses and social partners;
* corporate social responsibility;
* integration of economic, social and environmental components into the
* education for sustainable development;
* coherence of policies at all government and self-government levels;
* use of the best available technology;
* renewal (for example, by reuse or recycling) of natural resources;
* promotion of sustainable production and consumption;
* precaution and prevention;
